Wellness.Empowering Wellness, One Patient at a Time – DNP Wellness Clinic, Where Expertise Meets CompassionExplore Services About DNP Wellness Clinic Your Partner in Health and VitalityUnlock your best self with DNP Wellness Clinic. Whether you're aiming to shed weight to fit into your long-unworn favorite attire or revitalize through hormone replacement therapy, our clinic is committed to helping you achieve your health goals. Your journey to well-being starts with the expertise and compassion that define our practice. We work together to ensure that each patient receives the individualized attention they need.Our MissionAt DNP Wellness Clinic, our mission is to ensure every patient feels valued, appreciated, and respected, receiving top-quality care tailored to their unique needs. We aim to return to the days in healthcare where the patient was more than a number, treated as a unique individual with their own set of ideas, interests, and values. The goal of our clinic is for each patient to feel valued, appreciated, and respected while achieving high-quality care.Our ServicesExplore a comprehensive range of services tailored to meet your healthcare needs, including hormone replacement therapy, weight loss, botox treatments, acute care services, sports physicals, laser hair removal, tattoo removal, and laser therapy for hyperpigmented areas. Our integrated conventional approach ensures a holistic approach to health optimization. Our goal is to provide comprehensive care that addresses all of our patients' health needs. Book Your Appointment Now!Book Appointment OnlineCall Now ServicesDiscover a diverse range of services, including advanced skin treatments, tattoo removal, acute care, and rejuvenation options, all designed to enhance your well-being and confidence.Weight LossOur comprehensive weight loss services offer flexible options, available for individual purchase or as part of a package to support patients in achieving their goals. Our tailored techniques encompass a range of strategies including medication provision, fat percentage monitoring, personalized meal and exercise planning, and educational support to help you maintain your ideal weight. Take charge of your health and embark on a personalized weight loss journey with us.Hormone Replacement TherapyRestore hormonal levels to boost overall health and alleviate symptoms commonly associated with imbalances such as fatigue, brain fog, low motivation, listlessness, reduced libido, prolonged recovery, skin elasticity decline, and mood swings. Don't let these issues diminish your quality of life. Tailored treatment options including injectables, creams, patches, tablets, and pellets are available to suit individual preferences.Laser TreatmentsHarness the power of laser and pulsed light technology for effective skin treatments, including tattoo removal, targeting conditions like hyperpigmentation in melasma, acne scarring, and unwanted hair in areas such as the nose, face, armpits, chest, back, legs, and bikini area. Our laser treatments are also ideal for rejuvenation purposes, helping you regain a youthful appearance. Explore the transformative potential of laser therapy for radiant, healthier skin.Vitamin InjectionsDiscover our assortment of vitamin injections designed to enhance endurance, energy levels, libido, and support weight loss goals. She earned her Doctor of Nursing Practice in 2022, further enhancing her expertise. Keely's dedication extends beyond clinical practice; she has served as an educator and volunteered with the Red Cross at a military base in Hanau, Germany. About Premier NW Houston Medical Group Premier NW Houston Medical Group, located near Houston in Cypress, Texas, is a family medicine and primary care practice that provides comprehensive care for patients aged 18 and above. Also specializing in geriatric medicine and internal medicine services, the board-certified physicians and nurse practitioners at Premier NW Houston Medical Group practice preventive care that begins with thorough annual physical exams and other routine consultations, including well-woman exams. They offer screening for a range of cancers, as well as mental health conditions, dementia, and sexually transmitted diseases (STDs). The Premier NW Houston Medical Group team deals with both acute and chronic health conditions, from coughs and colds to high blood pressure and diabetes. They also provide services for specific groups of patients, including senior care, women's health, and chronic disease management. Patients benefit from the practice's onsite laboratory, which processes an extensive range of tests, including COVID-19 rapid antigen tests, antibody tests, and PCR tests, as well as rapid strep tests and influenza A and B tests. Phlebotomy, electrocardiogram, and spirometry services are also available for patient convenience and speedy diagnosis. Premier NW Houston Medical Group often has same-day appointment availability for sick visits and urgent health needs. They also offer state-of-the-art telemedicine services so patients who aren't able to visit the practice in person can still get the health care they need. At MD2 Austin Westlake, you'll be cared for by Dr. Jonathan Klocek and Dr. Scott Clitheroe, two of the most respected physicians in Austin. The physicians are affiliated with Seton Medical Center and St. David’s Hospital System and have long-standing ties with the top specialists in the area. Dr. Jonathan Klocek Dr. Jonathan Klocek is a highly sought-after primary care physician with over two decades of experience serving the Austin community. His loyal and longstanding patient base values his unwavering commitment to delivering compassionate, personalized care and unmatched medical leadership. In recognition of his devotion to his patients, he has received multiple awards and accolades throughout his career, including Texas Monthly Super Doctors and Austin Monthly Top Doctors. Dr. Klocek earned his undergraduate degree with High Honors in biochemistry from the University of Texas at Austin, graduating summa cum laude and Phi Beta Kappa – a rare and remarkable distinction. Following his residency, Dr. Klocek started his career as a hospitalist at Ascension Seton Medical Center, where he rose to the rank of Section Chief of the Department of Internal Medicine. Dr. Klocek is a member of the Texas Medical Association and the Travis County Medical Society. He is affiliated with Seton Medical Center. Dr. Clitheroe earned his undergraduate degree from the University of Texas at Austin and his medical degree from the University of Texas Medical School at Houston, where he graduated with multiple honors. Returning home to Austin to begin his medical career, Dr. Clitheroe was one of the first Hospitalists in the city. He founded Austin Hospital Physicians, where he remained president and CEO for over a decade. Before joining MD², he also served as the Medical Director for IPC, The Hospitalist Company, and Guiding Hospice.
